ReactJS State:
- By default react component has no state.
- To define a components initail state, we must have to add a class constructor.
- This assigns the initail state using this.state
- A state can later be changed by using setState function.

e.g. updateMsg() {
        this.setState({
            msg: "ReactJS"
        });
	}

- bind the this keyword to the updateMsg() function in the constructor.

e.g. this.updateMsg = this.updateMsg.bind(this);